{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6f269454-29c6-42aa-a3e7-f5f6c0114d08","content":"For a web API project, here are common templates and auth options:\n\n**Templates:**\n- **ASP.NET Core Web API** (`dotnet new webapi`) — most popular for .NET\n- **Express.js** (`express-generator`) — Node.js\n- **FastAPI** / **Flask** / **Django REST** — Python\n- **Spring Boot** — Java\n\n**Authentication options (ASP.NET Core example):**\n| Option | Flag |\n|---|---|\n| None | `--auth None` |\n| Individual accounts (Identity) | `--auth Individual` |\n| Azure AD (Entra ID) | `--auth SingleOrg` |\n| Azure AD B2C | `--auth IndividualB2C` |\n| Windows | `--auth Windows` |\n\n**Quick start example:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -n MyApi\n```\n\nWould you like help scaffolding a specific project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"144ca2c4-cefd-4831-a387-a0791051ceb1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":273,"requestId":"0406:1B1922:A773BA:D0B3FE:6A0128B4"},"id":"48bc58a9-49af-495e-adf1-41303dd578ce","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:54:20.104Z","parentId":"67cef2cb-72d3-47a4-91f2-e6cb169f1f44"}
